dspace-development.title: Ensure that submitted OAR Items with the workflow state for "Needs Review" be advanced to "Review" where necessary

comments.body:
The following should have resolved additional issues for Items missing the `dc.rights` metadata field were erroneously set from `needs review` to `reviewed`:

```
update workflowitem set state=3 where item_id in (select distinct(v.resource_id) from workflowitem as w inner join metadatavalue as v on v.resource_id=w.item_id where w.item_id=v.resource_id and w.state = 5 and v.resource_id not in (select distinct(v2.resource_id) from metadatavalue as v2 inner join metadatafieldregistry as r2 on r2.metadata_field_id=v2.metadata_field_id where v2.text_value like '%Final published version%' and v2.resource_type_id=2 and r2.element='rights'));
```
Due to an issue which I cannot readily identify, the workflow step which is needed for the `Needs Review` state is `3`, while the `Reviewed` state value should be `4`.

dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: Missing Results for Specific Query

comments.body:
After reviewing the `Data source management` interface form, the synchronization seems to be inactive:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/277ef171-aef3-434e-9920-93481866fc47)

Further information was provided within the server logs with the following:

```bash
Log entry ID: 21bb7be5-9cb0-4cc1-8f35-ef9bff557be9
Logged at: 15:19:28.023 26/01/22

Level 1:
-------
Exception type: System.ServiceModel.EndpointNotFoundException
Message: There was no endpoint listening at net.pipe://localhost/elements-default/synchroniser that could accept the message. This is often caused by an incorrect address or SOAP action. See InnerException, if present, for more details.
Stack trace:
at System.Runtime.Remoting.Proxies.RealProxy.HandleReturnMessage(IMessage, IMessage)
at System.Runtime.Remoting.Proxies.RealProxy.PrivateInvoke(MessageData&, Int32)
at Symplectic.Elements.Sync.ApiClient.ISynchroniserApi.GetState()
at Symplectic.Elements.Sync.ApiClient.SynchroniserClient.GetState() in elements\Sync.ApiClient\SynchroniserClient.cs:line 33, char 4
at Symplectic.Elements.Website.Application.ErrorLoggingSynchroniserClient.GetState() in elements\Website.Application\ErrorLoggingSynchroniserClient.cs:line 43, char 5

Level 2:
-------
Exception type: System.IO.PipeException
Message: The pipe endpoint 'net.pipe://localhost/elements-default/synchroniser' could not be found on your local machine. 
Exception not yet thrown.
```

Manually executing the `Run` operation for the `Synchroniser` background service (this lies within the `Scheduled Jobs` interface form) led to the successful resynchronization of the data sources:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/65d86777-d0e7-485e-9b45-dd1f5aee4cbf)
![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/00803a9d-2d8c-4cbf-9764-e07751273d5e)

This was likely related to the Elements Scheduler system process not being running (please see #572)

This seems to still be requiring some time to reindex:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/8d05d5e3-ce44-4dd3-bac9-078e94e5aa52)

dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements server environment (cisdr201w) specifies that the Elements Scheduler is not running

comments.body:
There are several possible causes for this logged for the server:

- `DCOM was unable to communicate with the computer [$HOST] using any of the configured protocols; requested by PID      c2c (C:\windows\system32\taskhost.exe).`
- `The system failed to register host (A or AAAA) resource records (RRs) for network adapter
with settings:`
- `An SSL 3.0 connection request was received from a remote client application, but none of the cipher suites supported by the client application are supported by the server. The SSL connection request has failed.`

`The system failed to register host (A or AAAA) resource records (RRs) for network adapter with settings` seems unlikely to be the cause of this issue, as, through troubleshooting this, it would seem likely that this would lead to other issues related to server DNS record resolution (one *can* still access the server on the network).
Simply manually starting the `Elements Scheduler` does not (yet) seem to have triggered any error log entries. Perhaps this VM was rebooted at some point?
I shall reserve this for review for tomorrow morning, but this seems likely to be resolved.

princeton_ansible.title: Deduplicate role inclusion for molecule testing?

comments.body:
it's very curious. shouldn't ansible deduplicate the meta.yml entries and only run each once?

https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_reuse_roles.html#running-role-dependencies-multiple-times-in-one-play

I don't think Ansible deduplicates down the nested tree, and we have a lot of nested dependencies. For example, the dependency tree for the `lib_jobs` role looks like this:

- ruby (which depends on common)
- deploy_user (which also depends on common)
- mariadb (which depends on deploy_user ((which in turn depends on common)) )
- redis (no dependencies!!!)
- sidekiq_worker (which depends on rails_app ((which in turn depends on common, bind9, deploy_user, passenger, postgresql, nodejs. . . most of which have dependencies of their own)) )
- rails_app (which depends on common, bind9, deploy_user, passenger, postgresql, nodejs . . . see above)
- hr_share (which depends on samba)
Seems very thorough and clear 🎉  I think this is ready for merge whenever y'all are happy with it.
